main event: A civilian reported observing an unidentified object described as round and gold in color in Norwalk, California on 5 January 1965.
interesting points: The object was approximately 30 feet in diameter, The object was stationary with an unknown duration, No physical evidence was obtained from the sighting, The initial report lacked sufficient details for a thorough investigation, The sighting was noted as needing more information for evaluation.
witness description: Jacob Stein observed the object directly overhead for about 15 seconds.
